<% provide(:title, "Global stock threshold") %>

<div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">
    <nav class="flex mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="inline-flex items-center space-x-1 md:space-x-2 rtl:space-x-reverse">
            <li class="inline-flex items-center">
                <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 hover:text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 dark:hover:text-white" do %>
                    <svg class="w-3 h-3 me-2.5" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path d="m19.707 9.293-2-2-7-7a1 1 0 0 0-1.414 0l-7 7-2 2a1 1 0 0 0 1.414 1.414L2 10.414V18a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h3a1 1 0 0 0 1-1v-4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h2a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v4a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h3a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7.586l.293.293a1 1 0 0 0 1.414-1.414Z"/>
                    </svg>
                    Home
                <% end %>
            </li>
            <li>
                <div class="flex items-center">
                    <svg class="rtl:rotate-180 w-3 h-3 text-gray-400 mx-1" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 6 10">
                        <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m1 9 4-4-4-4"/>
                    </svg>
                    <%= link_to 'Items setting', items_setting_path, class: "text-sm font-medium text-orange-700 hover:text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 dark:hover:text-white" %>
                </div>
            </li>
            <li aria-current="page">
                <div class="flex items-center">
                    <svg class="rtl:rotate-180 w-3 h-3 text-gray-400 mx-1" aria-hidden="true" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 6 10">
                        <path stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="m1 9 4-4-4-4"/>
                    </svg>
                    <span class="ms-1 text-sm font-medium text-gray-500 md:ms-2 dark:text-gray-400">Global stock threshold</span>
                </div>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </nav>

    <h2 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 flex items-center">Update global stock threshold <button data-popover-target="popover-animation" data-popover-placement="bottom-end" type="button"><svg class="w-4 h-4 ms-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-gray-500" aria-hidden="true" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-8-3a1 1 0 00-.867.5 1 1 0 11-1.731-1A3 3 0 0113 8a3.001 3.001 0 01-2 2.83V11a1 1 0 11-2 0v-1a1 1 0 011-1 1 1 0 100-2zm0 8a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2z" clip-rule="evenodd"></path></svg><span class="sr-only">Show information</span></button></h2>

    <div data-popover id="popover-animation" role="tooltip" class="absolute z-50 invisible inline-block text-sm text-gray-500 transition-opacity duration-300 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-3xl shadow-md opacity-0 md:w-1/2 dark:bg-gray-800 dark:border-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <div class="p-3 space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Stock Threshold</h3>
            <p>A stock threshold is the minimum quantity of stock that is considered acceptable before replenishment or restocking is necessary. It serves as a warning point, triggering alerts or notifications when the stock level falls below the set threshold. This allows for timely reordering or restocking, preventing stockouts and ensuring a steady supply of goods.</p>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Item Stock Threshold</h3>
            <p>An item stock threshold is the minimum quantity of a specific item that is considered acceptable. It is set individually for each item and takes precedence over the global stock threshold. When the stock level of an item falls below its set threshold, it triggers a warning or alert, indicating that replenishment or restocking of that item is necessary.</p>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Global Stock Threshold</h3>
            <p>A global stock threshold is the default minimum quantity of stock that applies to all items without a specifically set item stock threshold. It serves as a fallback threshold, ensuring that all items have a minimum stock level, even if an individual item threshold is not set. The global stock threshold provides a safety net, preventing stockouts and ensuring a steady supply of goods across all items.</p>
        </div>
        <div data-popper-arrow></div>
    </div>

    <div class="">
        <%= form_with model: current_user, url: update_global_stock_threshold_settings_path, method: :patch do |f| %>

            <div class="my-5">
                <%= f.number_field :global_stock_threshold, class: "mt-2 text-sm w-full px-3 p-2.5 border rounded-md dark:bg-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 dark:focus:bg-gray-800 border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-700 dark:focus:border-emerald-400 dark:focus:ring-emerald-400" %>
            </div>

            <%= f.submit "Update threshold", class: "w-full md:w-auto px-8 py-3 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-sm rounded-md text-white bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-offset-2 focus:ring-blue-600 dark:bg-emerald-400 dark:hover:bg-emerald-500 dark:text-gray-900 dark:focus:ring-emerald-400 dark:focus:ring-offset-current" %>
        <% end %>
    </div>
</div>
